{
  "$comment": "Ground truth for the recall (false-negative depth) benchmark — see docs/validation/recall-benchmark.md and packages/core/test/recall.test.ts. Each file maps to the quantum-vulnerable crypto it TRULY contains, labeled independently of what the detectors match, across a deliberate spread of difficulty (canonical/aliased/uncommon/config/adversarial). Family vocabulary: RSA, DH, ECDH, ECDSA, DSA, EDDSA, X25519, X448, SECP256K1, TLS, SSH, DEP.",

  "recall/go/x509_keyutils.go": {
    "language": "go",
    "expected": [
